message.content: cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.ET - This paper discusses the complexity and structural properties of one-tape linear-time Turing machines, which are closely related to finite state automata. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), logic in computer science (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), and emerging technologies (cs.ET).
